article.headline: NC A&amp,T 77, W. Virginia St. 0
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- North Carolina A&T set a school single-game scoring record Saturday night and demolished West Virginia State 77-0 in a non-conference mismatch. The Aggies had 10 rushing touchdowns, running for 313 yards. Six players rushed for touchdowns. Dominique Drake scored three times while Mike Mayhew and Lewis Kindle each scored twice. Ricky Phillips returned an interception 19 yards for one of the Aggies' 11 touchdowns. After a season-opening loss to Coastal Carolina, North Carolina A&T toyed with the Division II Yellow Jackets (1-1). Drake, Kindle and Mayhew each rushed for a touchdown in the first quarter. They did so again in the second period. It was 42-0 at halftime. The Aggies scored four more touchdowns in the third quarter. Kindle, the starting quarterback who was suspended for the opener, completed 10 of 15 passes for 176 yards. The Aggies held West Virginia State to two first downs and 41 total yards.
